CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "Friends, But On Different Tickets - Alex Lee, the florist, and Democratic candidate for alderman, is trying to tell Charles D. Clark, Republican candidate for constable, something about what could happen last Tuesday. Lucius Davenport, Republican aldermanic aspirant, doesn't seem too much interested.  Lee was also satisfied with a token vote for himself as he plugged for Thomas J. Smith for constable. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Alex Lee smoking cigar, Charles D. Clark, and Lucius Davenport, standing on sidewalk in front of automobiles and James T. Goode for constable political office, during 1955 primary elections
